## Attempt 1 (this patch)

Removed `self._is_fp8_kv_cache` from the flatten condition in
`vllm/v1/attention/backends/mla/flashinfer_mla.py _build_decode` so that
FP8 + spec-verify (tpr>1) stays a single request and trtllm-gen handles
the causal mask internally.

```python
# BEFORE (triggers flatten → XQA → 0% acceptance):
if num_decode_tokens > num_reqs and (
    self._is_fp8_kv_cache
    or (
        self.dcp_world_size > 1
        and dcp_tot_seq_lens_device is not None
    )
):

# AFTER (no flatten for FP8 spec; trtllm-gen takes tpr>1 natively):
if num_decode_tokens > num_reqs and (
    self.dcp_world_size > 1
    and dcp_tot_seq_lens_device is not None
):
```

## Result: breaks startup on sm120 fp8

Server crashes with:
```
ValueError: Supported block_size are 32 and 64, got 16
  …/flashinfer/…/trtllm_batch_decode_with_kv_cache_mla
```

i.e. trtllm-gen's FP8 MLA decode kernel on sm120 requires KV block_size ∈
{32, 64}; the default `--block-size` that vLLM selects for TRITON_MLA fp8 is
16 and FlashInfer-MLA's supported_kernel_block_sizes accepts MultipleOf(16),
so it does not get bumped at config-selection time. The XQA path (used by
the flatten branch) *does* work at block_size=16, which is why the buggy
flatten-based path even exists.

## Next steps to pursue

Either:

(a) **Bump block_size to 64 when FLASHINFER_MLA is selected.** Look at the
    backend's `get_supported_kernel_block_sizes()` (line ~475) and see why
    the selector happily gives it a block_size of 16. Likely needs to be
    `[32, 64]` or `MultipleOf(32)` so the kv_cache allocator picks 32/64.
    Then the FP8 trtllm-gen path works with real per-request seq_lens.

(b) **Fix XQA's handling of flattened spec-verify tokens.** This is the
    current (broken) path. It treats each flattened token as an independent
    request; causal masking within the span is not applied. Would need a
    patch inside the flashinfer kernel (beyond our scope here), or to
    explicitly refuse the XQA path when tpr>1 (fall through to trtllm-gen
    only, combined with (a)).

Recommendation: try (a) first by forcing `--block-size 64` at the vllm
serve command line when using FLASHINFER_MLA + MTP. If that runs, verify
draft acceptance > 0 at 30k ctx and measure tok/s. The expected result is
flat ~19 ms interarrival and ~120+ tok/s with correct acceptance.
